Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.ui

Class PageConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eclipsesource.tabris.ui.PageConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.eclipse.rap.rwt.Adaptable
    public class PageConfiguration
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.eclipse.rap.rwt.Adaptable, java.io.Serializable

    Page objects will be instantiated by the framework. Therefore you need to be able to configure such a Page in a convenient way before it's actually created. This is the single purpose of a PageConfiguration. It provides methods to define the visual role in a UI e.g. the page image that's used in a menu or if the page should be a top level page or not. When a Page contains actions the PageConfiguration is also the right place to add them represented by an ActionConfiguration.

    PageConfiguration objects will be usually added to a UIConfiguration.

    Since:
    0.11
    See Also:
    Page, ActionConfiguration, UIConfiguration, Serialized Form

      • PageConfiguration

        public PageConfiguration​(java.lang.String pageId,
                         java.lang.Class<? extends Page> pageType)

        Creates a new PageConfiguration object with the defined id and a Page type. The id needs to be unique within the Tabris UI because you will need to use them to browse through the several pages using the UI.

        Parameters:
        pageId - the unique id of the Page. Must not be empty or null.
        pageType - the type of the Page to be created. Must not be null.
        Since:
        1.0
